reviews.review_text:
Road Trip My room mates and I were living in Golden, CO having moved there six months prior from NJ. Let's go see the GD out west.  Packed up and ventured out.  The first night was terrific but the second night was special.  Sugaree opener, they could have taken a break and I'd been happy.
Anyway, two at the Hall and on 12/30 Pauley Pavillion for what was another barn burner.  Did not have tix for the NYE show at Winterland so we headed home energized for the forthcoming 1979.  That's my story and I'm sticking to it. The Golden Hall is such a grand venue.  I just remember the sound being so awesome (maybe it was the powder lsd we digested).  "Gone are the days".....Go well my compadres...
